WEBVTT

00:03:28.960 --> 00:03:31.816
They just end up hanging out
with their existing friends.

00:03:31.840 --> 00:03:33.376
At company parties

00:03:33.400 --> 00:03:37.096
people mostly just get closer
to the colleagues who are similar to them.

00:03:37.120 --> 00:03:39.976
And those people,
the ones you like the most?

00:03:40.000 --> 00:03:42.280
Odds are, you rely on them
more than you should.

00:03:43.080 --> 00:03:45.736
Think about the last time
you reached out to a colleague

00:03:45.760 --> 00:03:48.680
for everyday advice, help
or ideas on solving a problem.

00:03:49.280 --> 00:03:50.520
Who did you go to?

00:03:51.160 --> 00:03:52.816
In a study at a tech company

00:03:52.840 --> 00:03:55.696
it turned out that people went
to the colleagues they liked,

00:03:55.720 --> 00:03:57.576
regardless of their competence.

00:03:57.600 --> 00:03:59.736
I found something similar in a hospital.

00:03:59.760 --> 00:04:02.536
When nurses wanted
a second opinion on a diagnosis,